ame. The index is set to the hourly timestamps."]}, {"name": "cloudside.hydra.get_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "station_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "folder", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "raw_folder", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "force_download", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Download and parse full records from Portland's Hydra Network\n\n# Parameters\n\nstation_id\n\n: Short name of the rain gauge. To locate this, go to the\n  [Hydra Click Map](https://or.water.usgs.gov/non-usgs/bes/raingage_info/clickmap.html),\n  select your site, and inspect the final URL for the HTML in file.\n  For example, for Hydra Site #3, which has this URL:\n  <https://or.water.usgs.gov/non-usgs/bes/sauvies_island.html>,\n  you would pass `\"sauvies_island\"` as the station ID.\n\nfolder\n\n: This is the top-level directory where data will be saved.\n\nraw_folder\n\n: This is a subdirectory where the raw data will be downloaded.\n\nforce_download\n\n: See to the True to force re-downloading of data that already exists\n  in the folder specified structure.\n\n# Returns\n\nrain_df\n\n: Dataframe with the hourly rainfall depth in inches. The column label\n  will be the *station_id*. The index is set to the hourly timestamps.\n\n# See also\n\n<https://or.water.usgs.gov/non-usgs/bes/>\n<https://or.water.usgs.gov/non-usgs/bes/raingage_info/clickmap.html>\n<https://or.water.usgs.gov/non-usgs/bes/rainfall_data_quality.html>\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cloudside.tests.test_hydra", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "cloudside.tests.test_hydra.expected_hydra", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.tests.test_hydra.test_parse_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "expected_hydra", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.tests.test_hydra.test_get_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fetcher", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "checker", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "getter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos", "documentation": ["std lib stuff"], "functions": [{"name": "cloudside.asos.value_or_not", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obs_attr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos._process_sky_cover", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos._fetch_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "station_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timestamp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ftp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raw_folder", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "force_download", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "past_attempts", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_attempts", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Fetches a single file from the ASOS ftp and returns its pathh on the\nlocal file system\n\nParameters\n----------\nstation_id : str\n    The station ID/airport code of the gauge\ntimestamp : datetime-like\n    A pandas `Timestamp` or other datetime-like object with `.year` and\n    `.month` attributes\nftp : FTP-connection\n    Connection to the FAA/ASOS ftp server\nraw_folder : pathlib.Path\n    Directory on the local file system where the data should be saved\nforce_download : bool (default is False)\n    See to the True to force re-downloading of ASOS data that already\n    exist\n\nReturns\n-------\ndst_path : pathlib.Path\n    Object representing the location of the downloaded file's location on\n    the local file system"]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.fetch_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "station_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "startdate", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stopdate", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "email", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raw_folder", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "force_download", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pbar_fxn", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Fetches a single file from the ASOS ftp and returns its path on the\nlocal file system\n\nParameters\n----------\nstation_id : str\n    The station ID/airport code of the gauge\nstartdate, stopdate : datetime-like\n    Pandas `Timestamp` or other datetime-like objects with `.year` and\n    `.month` attributes representing the date range (inclusive) of data\n    to be downloaded\nemail : str\n    Your email address to be used as the ftp login password\nraw_folder : pathlib.Path\n    Directory on the local file system where the data should be saved\nforce_download : bool (default is False)\n    See to the True to force re-downloading of ASOS data that already\n    exist\npbar_fxn : callable, optional\n    A tqdm-like progress bar function such as `tqdm.tqdm` or\n    `tqdm.tqdm_notebook`.\n\nReturns\n-------\nraw_paths : list of pathlib.Path\n    list of objects representing the location of the downloaded files'\n    locations on the local file system"]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos._find_reset_time", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "precip_ts", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Determines the precipitation gauge's accumulation reset time.\n\nParameters\n----------\nprecip_ts : pandas.Series\n    Time series of the raw precipitation data.\n\nReturns\n-------\nrt : int\n    The minute of the hour which is most likely the reset time for the\n    chunk of data."]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos._process_precip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rt", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raw_precipcol", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Processes precip data that accumulates hourly into raw minute\nintensities.\n\nParameters\n----------\ndata : pandas.DataFrame\nrt : int\n    Minute of the hour at which the gauge's hourly accumulation is reset\nraw_precipcol : str\n    Label of the column in `data` that contains the raw (hourly acummulated)\n    precipitation data.\n\nReturns\n-------\nprecip : pandas.Series\n    Cleaned up precip record with instaneous 5-min rainfall depths"]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.parse_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_precipcol", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parses a raw ASOS/METAR file into a pandas.DataFrame\n\nParameters\n----------\nfilepath : str or pathlib.Path object of the METAR file\nnew_precipcol : str\n    The desired column label of the precipitation column after it has been\n    disaggregated from hourly accumulations\n\nReturns\n-------\ndf : pandas.DataFrame"]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.get_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "station_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "startdate", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stopdate", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "email", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "folder", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "raw_folder", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "force_download", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pbar_fxn", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Download and process a range of FAA/ASOS data files for a given station\n\n# Parameters\n\nstation_id\n\n: The station ID/airport code of the gauge\n\nstartdate, stopdate\n\n: Pandas `Timestamp` or other datetime-like objects with `.year` and\n  `.month` attributes representing the date range (inclusive) of data\n  to be downloaded\n\nemail\n\n: Your email address to be used as the ftp login password\n\nfolder\n\n: Top-level folder to store all of the transferred ftp data\n\nraw_folder\n\n: Directory on the local file system where the data should be saved\n\nforce_download\n\n: See to the True to force re-downloading of data that already exists\n  in the folder specified structure.\n\npbar_fxn\n\n: A tqdm-like progress bar function such as `tqdm.tqdm` or\n  `tqdm.tqdm_notebook`.\n\n# Returns\n\nweather : pandas.DataFrame\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> from cloudside import asos\n>>> from tqdm import tqdm\n>>> pdx = asos.get_data('KPDX', '2013-09-01', '2013-10-31', 'iamweather@sensors.net',\n...                     folder='Portland_weather', raw_folder='asos_files',\n...                     force_download=False, pbar_fxn=tqdm)\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "cloudside.asos._fields", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.Obs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos._logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.HOURLY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.MONTHLY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.FIVEMIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "cloudside.asos.MetarParser", "bases": ["Metar.Metar"], "methods": [{"name": "cloudside.asos.MetarParser.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.MetarParser._unparsed_group_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Handle otherwise unparseable main-body groups."]}, {"name": "cloudside.asos.MetarParser.d